Q2/- How many scopes are there for a Spring Bean, which is the default scope for a Spring
     Bean? Explain with an example.
     
     
Answer:- There are 4 scope for a bean:-
         
         1.Singleton scope.
         2.Prototype scope.
         3. request scope
         4. session scope
         
         Singleton is the default scope for a Spring Bean.
         
         Example:- A obj1 = ctx.getBean("a1",A.class);
                   A obj2 = ctx.getBean("a1",A.class);
                   System.out.println(obj1 == obj2); //true
